Question 1: Library Management System (Abstract Classes)
Instructions:
Create an abstract class LibraryItem with attributes:

String itemID: Unique ID for the item.
String title: Title of the item.
Abstract methods:
void displayItemDetails(): Displays item details.
void borrowItem(): Marks the item as borrowed.
void returnItem(): Marks the item as returned.
Create subclasses:

Book: Adds String author and boolean isBorrowed to indicate borrowing status.
DVD: Adds String director and boolean isBorrowed.
Allow users to:

Add items (books/DVDs).
Borrow or return items.
View item details.

Options:
1. Add Book
2. Add DVD
3. View Item Details
4. Borrow Item
5. Return Item
6. Exit
Choose an option: 1
Enter Book ID: B001
Enter Book Title: Java Programming
Enter Author Name: John Doe
Book added successfully.

Options:
